fields.name: AccessedAt
fields.description: Last time there was a receive request to this subscription.

fields.name: AutoDeleteOnIdle
fields.description: ISO 8061 timeSpan idle interval after which the topic is automatically deleted. The minimum duration is 5 minutes.

fields.name: ClientAffineProperties
fields.description: Properties specific to client affine subscriptions.

fields.name: CreatedAt
fields.description: Exact time the message was created.

fields.name: DeadLetteringOnFilterEvaluationExceptions
fields.description: Value that indicates whether a subscription has dead letter support on filter evaluation exceptions.

fields.name: DeadLetteringOnMessageExpiration
fields.description: Value that indicates whether a subscription has dead letter support when a message expires.

fields.name: DefaultMessageTimeToLive
fields.description: ISO 8061 Default message timespan to live value. This is the duration after which the message expires, starting from when the message is sent to Service Bus. This is the default value used when TimeToLive is not set on a message itself.

fields.name: DuplicateDetectionHistoryTimeWindow
fields.description: ISO 8601 timeSpan structure that defines the duration of the duplicate detection history. The default value is 10 minutes.

fields.name: EnableBatchedOperations
fields.description: Value that indicates whether server-side batched operations are enabled.

fields.name: ForwardDeadLetteredMessagesTo
fields.description: Queue/Topic name to forward the Dead Letter message

fields.name: ForwardTo
fields.description: Queue/Topic name to forward the messages

fields.name: IsClientAffine
fields.description: Value that indicates whether the subscription has an affinity to the client id.

fields.name: LockDuration
fields.description: ISO 8061 lock duration timespan for the subscription. The default value is 1 minute.

fields.name: RequiresSession
fields.description: Value indicating if a subscription supports the concept of sessions.

fields.name: UpdatedAt
fields.description: The exact time the message was updated.
